  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This synthetic adversarial package embeds a future-dated evidence node (W-CON-03): one ValidationResult carries an evidenceTimestamp of 2027-03-15T09:00:00Z, which is strictly after the UnitOfAssurance signatureTimestamp of 2024-11-20T14:30:00Z. The narrative does not address this discrepancy.",
